<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06277008 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06277008 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  REAL-ESTATE; COMPANY; CHANGE; FINANCE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  CB Commercial Real Estate Group Inc., hit hard by the recession, has announceda restructuring that will help reduce its costs by more than $49 million overthree years.;   &quot;Real estate transactions are at very depressed levels,&quot; JesseHarrill, CB's senior vice president of communications, said Wednesday. &quot;No oneanticipated how bad this crunch would be.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  CB SEEKS TO REDUCE COSTS BY $49 MILLION  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Commercial Real Estate  </MEMO><TEXT>     As part of the restructuring, CB will close its Long Island, N.Y.,Bethesda, Md., and Mid-Wilshire in Los Angeles offices, and a handful ofadministrative staff members were laid off.;   CB, the largest commercial realestate brokerage in the nation, said it has renegotiated the interest on$230.4 million in debt, which will save about $7 million a year in interest,from $27 million to $20 million, CB said.;   In addition, the top 10executives are taking a pay cut, ranging from 3 percent to 20 percent forChairman and Chief Executive Jim Didion, whose salary CB did not disclose.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Los Angeles Daily News  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Los Angeles  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911003  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2E  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  160  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, October 3, 199100277008,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>